{ How to continue here? } 9... b5 $1 { We are happy to give up the b5 pawn to get back control over the center. } 10. e5 ( 10. Nxb5 Nxe4 { white has to be careful not to get worse here as he is down a pawn with just temporary activity in return. } 11. Ba5 ( 11. Ne5 Bb7 12. Ba5 Qc8 13. Nxc4 Nxg3 14. hxg3 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Qb7+ $11 ) ( 11. Qc2 Rb8 12. Nxa7 Bb7 $11 ) 11... Nb6 12. Ne5 ( 12. Qe2 Nd6 $15 ) 12... Bb7 13. Qc2 ( 13. Qe2 Qd5 $11 ) 13... Nd6 { The position will simplify now with a lot of exchanges. } 14. Bxb7 Nxb7 15. Bxb6 cxb6 16. Qxc4 Nd6 17. Nxd6 Qxd6 $11 ) 10... Nd5 11. Nxb5 { white has won back the pawn but we get the semi-open 'b' file and activity in return. We will play on the queenside keeping the d5 square under control. } *

