{How to continue here?} 11... g5 $1 {We can hunt down the dark-squared bishop now!} 12. Be3 Ng4 {We execute our idea, winning the dark-squared bishop by force. Next, we can continue playing on the kingside with our king secure on the dark-squares.} 13. Nf1 Nxe3 14. Nxe3 h5 15. h3 Kg7 16. Qd3 (16. Bh1 Rh8 17. Qd3 Nf8 $15 {black went on to convert in the game 0-1 (61) Ziechaus, L (2106) -Bowley, M ICCF email 2021.}) 16... Rh8 17. cxd5 cxd5 18. Rc3 Nf8 $11 {black is the one with the initiative in my opinion. We can also go b5 on the queenside.} *


