{ How to continue here? } 11... Ne4 $1 { We shift plans and get our knight to the active e4 post. white has wasted time with his bishop. However, keep in mind that we are not going to go f5 blindly next. } 12. Bb2 ( 12. Ne5 Nxe5 13. Bxe4 { This looks strong but we have the nice resource- } 13... f5 $1 14. Bg2 ( 14. Bxf5 Rxf5 15. dxe5 Qe8 $15 { The light squares are a big issue on the kingside. } ) 14... Ng4 15. Nd2 f4 { The benefit of our pawn structure in the center is that it keeps the position semi closed and allows us to play more freely on the kingside. } 16. Nf3 fxg3 17. hxg3 Bd6 $11 ) ( 12. Nbd2 { gives up the bishop very easily. } 12... Nxc3 13. Qxc3 Bb7 $11 ) 12... f5 { With the bishop on b2 it makes perfect sense to start our play on the kingside. f4 also becomes an idea for us. } 13. Nc3 Qe8 $1 { The queen prepares to head over to the kingside soon. 1/2-1/2 (37) Ludgate,A (2513) -Germanes,R (2518) FICGS email 2022 } *
