{How to continue here?} 10... a5 $1 {We go a5 before putting our bishop on a6 avoiding white's a4-a5 plan. Now again it is not easy for white to develop his knight.} (10... Ba6 11. a4 $1) 11. Bf4 (11. Nc3 Ba6 $11 {[%csl Rc4]}) 11... Ba6 12. Nbd2 (12. Ne5 Rc8 $11) 12... Nh5 13. Be3 Rc8 {We have the idea to go f5-f4 next. white has to be careful.} 14. Ne5 Nhf6 15. Ndf3 Nxe5 16. Nxe5 Re8 $11 {We will continue slowly with Bd6 and h6. I do not see a good plan for white.} *


