{How to continue here?} 15... Ndc5 $1 {The is a very interesting piece sacrifice exploiting white's lack of co-ordination.} 16. dxc5 bxc5 {The threat now is to go c4 and win the knight on b5. Also, Bc6 or a6 are quite dangerous. white has two ways to retreat with the bishop.} 17. Bf4 (17. Be5 c4 18. Qa4 f6 19. Bd4 e5 {I love this position! We get a huge advantage in the center and are likely to win back the piece on b5.} 20. Bxa7 Nd6 21. Nc3 Qxa4 22. Nxa4 Ra8 {white loses a piece and he has to start playing in defence.} 23. Bc5 Rxa4 24. Nd2 {There are a few different ways to continue here. The pawn on c4 is hanging right now.} Rb8 (24... Rc8 25. Bxd6 Bxd6 26. b3 Ra7 27. bxc4 Bb4 $11) 25. e4 dxe4 26. Bxd6 Bxd6 27. Nxc4 Bc5 28. Nxe5 Bd4 29. Nd7 Rba8 30. Rc7 Bd5 31. Rd1 Bxa2 32. Bxe4 Bxf2+ 33. Kxf2 Rxe4 $11) 17... c4 18. Qa4 {I reached this position in a Titled Tuesday game but got confused with less time.} Bc5 {We go after the pawn on f2 and now Bc6 is a huge threat.} (18... Bc6 $2 {allows} 19. Nfd4 Bc5 20. Nxc6 $18 {1-0 (46) Svane,R (2637) -Arjun,K (2532) Chess.com INT 2022}) 19. b3 (19. Be3 {also does not change much.} Bc6 20. Nfd4 (20. Bxc5 Bxb5 21. Qxa7 Nxc5 $11) 20... Bxd4 21. Bxd4 Bxb5 22. Qxa7 Ra8 23. Qc7 f6 {The rook will join the game via f7 next.} 24. Bxe4 dxe4 25. Bc3 {1/2-1/2 (31) Lazavik,D (2553) -Sadhwani,R (2603) Chess.com INT 2023} e5 $11 {[%cal Ge8c6]}) 19... Bc6 20. bxc4 dxc4 21. Qxc4 Bxf2+ 22. Kf1 e5 $1 {There are a lot of tactics in the air here.} 23. Nxe5 (23. Bg5 Bb6 24. Qb4 Qe6 25. Rxc6 Qxc6 26. Nxe5 Qc5 27. Qxc5 Rxc5) 23... Nd2+ 24. Bxd2 Bxg2+ 25. Kxf2 Rxc4 26. Nxc4 Qxb5 27. Kxg2 Rc8 $11 {The endgame is roughly balanced with white's lead in material compensated by his weak king.} *

