{How to continue here?} 21... Nd2 $1 {A nice tactical idea to equalise. We place our knight on an awkward square but it helps us activate our queen.} (21... Nxe5 22. dxe5 Qb6 23. Qf3 Nc5 24. h4 $16) 22. Be2 Nxe5 23. dxe5 Qd4 {We are already up a pawn and unless white does something immediately we are much better.} 24. Rac1 Rb8 25. Rc2 Rb1 {We manage to exchange the rooks just in time but our knight is misplaced in enemy territory.} 26. Rxb1 Nxb1 27. Qd6 (27. Qc5 Rd8 28. Qxd4 Rxd4 29. Rxc6 Nd2 30. Rc2 Kg7 $11) 27... Qe4 28. Bd3 Qf3 29. Be2 Qe4 30. Bd3 Qf3 $11 {1/2-1/2 (30) Nyvlt,Z (2425) -Savoca,A (2458) ICCF email 2018} *


