{How to continue here?} 14... g5 $1 {We go after the dark-squared bishop.} (14... f5 15. exf6 Nxf6 16. Qa4 Bb7 17. Nd2 Qe8 18. Qxe8 Rfxe8 19. Nc4 Ba6 20. Ne5 Rac8 {1/2-1/2 (29) Giri,A (2783) -Ding,L (2813) Wijk aan Zee 2019}) 15. Bxg4 (15. Qa4 Bc4 $1 16. b3 gxf4 17. Bxg4 b5 {The queen is in trouble on the queenside.} 18. Qa6 Bc5 19. bxc4 Qg5 20. Qxb5 Rac8 21. cxd5 fxg3 22. hxg3 f5 $1 23. Qb3 fxg4 $36 {The complications continue but white is the one at risk here.}) 15... gxf4 16. Qa4 (16. gxf4 $4 Kh8 $19) (16. Nd2 f5 $1 17. exf6 Rxf6 $40 {[%csl Rg1][%cal Gg8h8]}) 16... Bc4 $1 {We block the queen from swinging over to the kingside.} 17. Nd2 b5 18. Qc2 (18. Qa6 fxg3 19. hxg3 Bb4 20. Ne4 Qc7 21. Nf6+ Kg7 22. b3 (22. Nxd5 Bxd5 23. Rxd5 exd5 24. Qf6+ Kg8 25. Qg5+ Kh8 $11) 22... Rab8 $1 23. bxc4 Rb6 24. Qxb6 axb6 25. cxd5 Qxe5 {The position is dynamically balanced but I prefer black.}) 18... Rc8 19. Nf3 Bxa2 $1 {We need this pawn to get our bishop to b3.} 20. Qd2 Bb3 21. Rdc1 Rc4 {This is a nice square for the rook and we would love to recapture with the 'd' pawn.} 22. gxf4 (22. Rxc4 dxc4 23. Qxf4 a5 24. h4 a4 25. Nd4 Qd7 $11) 22... Kh8 23. h3 Rg8 24. Kh2 a5 $11 {[%cal Ga5a4]} *


