{How to continue here?} 19... g5 $1 {The direct approach to open the 'g' file.} (19... Bd6 $5 {[%cal Gg7g5]} 20. Ng3 h5 $1 {We would love for white to take on h5 and open the file for our rook.} 21. Kh1 (21. Nxh5 Qh4 22. Ng3 g5 $17 {[%cal Gc7h7]}) 21... g5 22. Qc3 h4 $13) 20. fxg5 Bxg5 21. Kh1 Rg8 {We can continue with either Rg6-h6 or get our queen into the game with Bh6 and Qh4. The position is dynamically balanced with our weaknesses compensated by our play on the kingside.} 22. Rg1 (22. Bf3 Rg6 23. b4 Bh6 $11 {The queen is ready to jump to h4 next.}) (22. b4 Bh6 23. f4 Bf8 24. Rg1 Bxb4 25. d5 Qf6 26. dxc6 Bc5 27. Nd4 Bxd4 28. exd4 Qxd4 29. Rcd1 Qxf4 {1/2-1/2 (29) Perez Lopez,A (2412) -Genga,S (2423) ICCF email 2018}) 22... c5 23. Bf3 Rg6 {There are several different options here to play black.} 24. Ng3 f4 25. Ne4 fxe3 26. Nxg5 Rxg5 27. fxe3 Rxg1+ 28. Rxg1 cxd4 29. Qe4 Qf6 30. Qg4 Rg7 31. Qxg7+ Qxg7 32. Rxg7 Kxg7 33. exd4 $11 {1/2-1/2 (35) Halliwell, T (2397) -Anokhin, Y (2417) ICCF email 2018} *

