{How to continue here?} 14... a5 $1 {This is a very important move actually. Let's see why.} (14... Z0 {I am adding a null move to showcase the point.} 15. Ng5 h6 16. Be4 f5 17. Nxe6 Qe8 18. Qxe8 Rxe8 19. Nc7 fxe4 20. Nxe8 $16) 15. Ng5 (15. g4 f6 $15) 15... h6 16. Be4 f5 17. Nxe6 Qe8 18. Qxe8 Rxe8 19. Nc7 fxe4 20. Nxe8 Na6 {We can continue with Nb6-d5 next. Our queenside pawns give us the edge here.} 21. Nd6 Nb6 22. Nxe4 Bh3 23. Ng2 a4 $15 {This may not look like a big advantage but our play on the queenside is very hard to stop.} *


