{How to continue here?} 17... c5 $1 {We are looking to undermine white's control over the center and moreover the f3 square is a weakness to exploit right now.} 18. Nxd5 exd5 19. Nd6 {white has to atleast try and win our dark-squared bishop.} Bxd6 (19... cxd4 20. Nf5 Rg8 21. Qxd4 Bb7 $11) 20. exd6 Nf6 21. Qf4 cxd4 22. Rxd4 Re8 {white's initiative has disappeared and he has to make sure that he does not get much worse.} 23. Bd2 Rb8 (23... Qa5 24. d7 Red8 25. Bh3 Bb5 26. Qe5 Bxd7 27. Bxd7 Nxd7 28. Qf5 Qb6 29. Rxd5 Nf6 30. Rb5 Qd4 31. Bxb4 Qxb2 $11) 24. Bg2 c3 25. bxc3 b3 {The b pawn is quite dangerous in the endgame.} 26. Bxd5 Nxd5 27. Rxd5 Bb7 28. Rb5 Bc6 29. c4 Qd7 30. Rxb8 Rxb8 31. Bc3 f6 $11 {black definitely has the upper hand here seeing the weaknesses in white's kingside.} *


