{ How to continue here? } 18... h5 $1 { We clear the back rank and gain space on the kingside. Now we can take on c5 next. } 19. Bb4 { The bishop is forced to defend the pawn awkwardly. } ( 19. Rfc1 { allows } 19... Rxa1 20. Rxa1 Nxc5 21. Bb4 Nb3 22. Nxb3 Rb8 $11 ) 19... Rfc8 ( 19... Ne5 { happened in the game 1-0 (31) Esipenko,A (2682) -Keymer,V (2686) Biel 2022 but it gives white some chances after } 20. Ba5 $14 ) 20. c6 ( 20. Rfc1 Nd5 21. c6 Ne5 22. Bc3 g5 $11 { We can go g4 next and get a bind on the kingside. } ) 20... Nb6 21. Rfc1 Rxa1 22. Rxa1 Nbd5 23. Be1 ( 23. Bc3 Ne4 $11 ) 23... Rb8 { It is not easy to defend b2 and also c6. } 24. Bc3 Ne4 25. Ra7 Rb6 26. Kf3 Ng5+ ( 26... Nexc3 27. bxc3 e5 $11 ) 27. Kg2 Ne4 $11 { Both sides can try to continue but a repetition is a fair result. Our pawn on h5 helps restrict the white king. } *
